just_use place_stack.go

# label: EARLY (collision-free placement)
# role: encodes domain knowledge — board geometry

Faithful Go port of `elm-port-docs/src/LynRummy/PlaceStack.elm`,
which ports `angry-cat/src/lyn_rummy/game/place_stack.ts`.

- `FindOpenLoc(existing, cardCount, bounds) Location` — sweeps a
  row-major grid from (0,0) at 10px step, returns the first
  (top, left) whose padded bounding box clears every existing
  stack. Fallback: bottom-left corner.
- `stackWidthForCount(n)` — mirrors Elm's `stackWidth`.

## Why Go needed its own copy

Tricks (`games/lynrummy/tricks/*`) create new stacks inside
`Apply()` — loose peels, new sets, split halves. Before this
module existed, those new stacks landed at `dummyLoc = (0,0)`,
overlapping the top-left stack every time. The referee caught
it (geometry stage), which killed `complete_turn` any turn a
trick produced a fresh stack.

## Pointers

- Consumers: `games/lynrummy/tricks/helpers.go` (`pushNewStack`,
  middle-of-run split branch), `games/lynrummy/tricks/pair_peel.go`
  (new-pair construction).
- Referee counterpart: `board_geometry.go` (`checkGeometry`).
  Same `BoardBounds` struct; placer uses it to stay inside.
- Not used by the Elm UI itself — the UI picks locations from
  cursor position. This is server-side only.
